Ever wondered what happens when you type https://www.google.com into your browser?

Join me on a quick tour behind the scenes of this seemingly simple operation to discover the amazing orchestration of technology involved:

1. DNS Lookup: Converts the domain name into an IP address.
2. TCP Connection: Establishes a reliable connection using TCP/IP protocols.
3. HTTPS/SSL Encryption: Secures the data exchange with SSL/TLS encryption.
4. Firewall: Monitors and controls network traffic to block malicious attempts.
5. Load Balancing: Distributes traffic across multiple servers to maintain performance.
6. Web and Application Servers: Manage HTTP requests and process application-specific logic.
7. Database Access: Retrieves necessary data like user preferences or search history.
8. Response Delivery: The web server sends the processed data back to your browser, displaying the page.

Each step involves complex interactions between various technological components to bring you a smooth and secure internet experience.

Stay tuned for more insights into how technology powers our daily web interactions!
